    <h1>Safety of the el&#xAD;derly &#x2022; Use non-slip ma&#xAD;te&#xAD;ri&#xAD;als in HDB toi&#xAD;lets</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210105/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-05"><time>2021-01-05</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sin­ga­pore is a grey­ing so­ci­ety. The risk of slip­ping in the toi­let is greater for the el­derly. But non-slip tiles are still not the de­fault op­tion in Hous­ing Board flat toi­lets.</p>
    <p>HDB should be for­ward-look­ing and sup­ply non-slip tiles in toi­lets.</p>
    <p>Sin­ga­pore is also a trop­i­cal coun­try where it rains fre­quently. Most pub­lic pave­ments sim­i­larly be­come slip­pery in the rain.</p>
    <p>To be more el­der-friendly, pave­ments should be lined with non-slip ma­te­ri­als.</p>
    <p>Safety must pre­cede aes­thet­ics. Goh Eng Chai</p>


</article>

